  "prompt": "Can dogs digest bones?",
  "response": "Dogs can digest some types of bones, but it largely depends on the type of bone and how it is prepared. Raw bones, especially those that are soft, like chicken or turkey necks, can typically be safe for dogs to chew on and digest. They are less likely to splinter and cause harm.\n\nHowever, cooked bones, particularly those that are hard and have been exposed to heat, can be very dangerous for dogs. Cooking can make bones brittle, causing them to splinter into sharp shards that can puncture a dog's digestive tract, leading to serious health issues such as choking, internal bleeding, or infection.\n\nIt's important to supervise your dog when they are chewing on bones and to consult with your veterinarian for recommendations specific to your dog's size, breed, and health condition. Always prioritize safety when it comes to your pet's diet.",
